opped up to keep the home fires burning, sacks of grain lugged off ships in the harbour, antisemitism and ethnic street-fighting, the padlocked doors of the Red Scare, his father’s first car. Gold tells the story of dating and marrying the love of his life, Evelyn, studying under the brilliant Sir Arnold Burgen, and his discovery of CEA (carcinoembryonic antigen) in a clear, fast-moving narrative that grips and fascinates. Gold’s Rounds also includes unforgettable stories from six decades of treating patients at the General, scenes from the founding of the famous Goodman Cancer Institute, and reflections on the physician's role and the meaning of a good death. By turns funny, wise, and heartrending, Gold’s memoir of a life well lived will be cherished by both medical professionals and general readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJewish physicianszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aPhysicianszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Medical.2bisacsh  a1934.  aAnthony Fauci.  aAnthony Jenkins.  aAuckie Sanft.  aBabbeh.  aBancroft.  aBaron Byng.  aBrian Mulroney.  aBurroughs Wellcome Fund.  aCEA.  aCeremony.  aChicken.  aCote St Luc.  aCouncil.  aCravenA.  aDEW Line.  aDeath.  aDinners.  aEmil Skamene.  aErma Bombeck.  aExpo 67.  aFame.  aGood.  aGoodman Cancer Institute.  aGraves.  aHall.  aHoffmann-La Roche.  aHolocaust.  aISOBM.  aIan Gold.  aInstitute.  aJane Fonda.  aJane Poulson.  aJazz.  aJoel Gold.  aJoseph Shuster.  aLaurentians.  aLife.  aMedical.  aMenschlichkeit.  aMila Mulroney.  aMill Hill.  aMolson.  aMonique Begin.  aMorris Winchevsky.  aNational.  aOptaw.  aOzarow.  aPoland.  aPontiac.  aRichard Cruess.  aRoddick Gates.  aRubber.  aRules.  aSam Fre